---
import Callout from "../../components/Callout.astro";
import OnThisPage from "../../components/OnThisPage.astro";
import Step from "../../components/Step.astro";
import TroubleshootItem from "../../components/TroubleshootItem.astro";
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
import { shortcuts } from "../../lib/site";
---

<Base
  title="OpenAI setup · Cloud Speech"
  description="Step-by-step OpenAI setup for the Cloud Speech browser extension: create an OpenAI account, generate an API key, and connect the extension."
  active="openai"
>
  <main class="relative mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-12">
    <p>
      <a class="link text-sm text-body" href="../../#guides">← Back to all guides</a>
    </p>

    <header class="mt-8">
      <p
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full bg-openai/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-body"
      >
        <span class="h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-openai"></span>
        Setup guide
      </p>
      <h1 class="mt-4 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">Set up OpenAI</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-body">
        OpenAI has expressive text-to-speech voices (tts-1, tts-1-hd, and gpt-4o-mini-tts) with
        the simplest setup of the four cloud providers: one API key, no region, no cloud console maze.
        It takes about 5 minutes.
      </p>
      <OnThisPage
        items={[
          { href: "#steps", label: "Setup steps" },
          { href: "#costs", label: "Costs" },
          { href: "#remove", label: "Remove access" },
          { href: "#troubleshooting", label: "Troubleshooting" },
        ]}
      />
    </header>

    <div class="card mt-8 p-5">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold">What you'll need</h2>
      <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-sm leading-relaxed text-body">
        <li>An OpenAI platform account with billing set up (there is no free tier for speech)</li>
        <li>About 5 minutes</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <ol
      id="steps"
      class="relative mt-12 scroll-mt-24 space-y-12 before:absolute before:top-2 before:bottom-2 before:left-4 before:w-px before:bg-fill"
    >
      <Step n={1} title="Create an OpenAI account">
        <ol class="list-decimal space-y-1.5 pl-5 marker:text-faint">
          <li>
            Go to
            <a class="link" href="https://platform.openai.com">platform.openai.com</a> and sign up
            (or sign in)
          </li>
          <li>
            Open <strong>Settings → Billing</strong> and add a payment method or buy prepaid
            credits; API access is pay-as-you-go and separate from ChatGPT subscriptions
          </li>
        </ol>
        <p class="text-muted">Tip: prepaid credits let you cap how much you can ever spend.</p>
      </Step>

      <Step n={2} title="Generate an API key">
        <ol class="list-decimal space-y-1.5 pl-5 marker:text-faint">
          <li>
            Go to
            <a class="link" href="https://platform.openai.com/api-keys"
              >platform.openai.com/api-keys</a
            >
          </li>
          <li>Click <strong>Create new secret key</strong></li>
          <li>Name it, e.g. <span class="value">Cloud Speech extension</span></li>
          <li>
            Click <strong>Create secret key</strong> and copy the key (it starts with
            <span class="value">sk-</span>)
          </li>
        </ol>
        <Callout title="Security warning">
          Copy the key immediately, because OpenAI will never show it again. Keep it secret; anyone with
          it can spend your credits. You can revoke it from the same page at any time.
        </Callout>
      </Step>

      <Step n={3} title="Connect the extension">
        <ol class="list-decimal space-y-1.5 pl-5 marker:text-faint">
          <li>Click the extension icon in your browser toolbar</li>
          <li>Open <strong>Settings → OpenAI</strong></li>
          <li>Paste your <strong>API key</strong></li>
          <li>Click <strong>Save &amp; test</strong></li>
        </ol>
        <p>
          Once the test passes, the OpenAI voices appear in the voice picker. Press ▶ to preview
          any voice and ★ to favorite the ones you like. Then highlight text on any page,
          right-click, and choose <em>Read aloud</em>, or press <kbd>{shortcuts.readAloud}</kbd>.
        </p>
        <Callout title="Good to know" tone="neutral">
          OpenAI voices support <strong>speed control only</strong>. The pitch and volume sliders
          don't apply to them (they do with Polly, Azure, and Google voices).
        </Callout>
      </Step>
    </ol>

    <!-- Costs -->
    <section class="card mt-12 scroll-mt-24 p-6" id="costs">
      <h2 class="flex items-center gap-2.5 text-lg font-semibold">
        <span class="h-2.5 w-2.5 rounded-full bg-openai"></span>
        Costs
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-body">
        OpenAI has <strong>no free tier</strong> for text-to-speech. As a rough guide,
        <strong>tts-1</strong> costs about <strong>$15 per 1 million characters</strong> and
        <strong>tts-1-hd</strong> about twice that. <strong>gpt-4o-mini-tts</strong> is billed
        differently, by text-input and audio-output tokens rather than characters, but works out
        roughly the same as tts-1 per minute of audio in practice. Check the
        <a class="link" href="https://platform.openai.com/docs/pricing"
          >official OpenAI pricing page</a
        >
        and our <a class="link" href="../../pricing/">provider comparison</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Remove access -->
    <section class="card mt-12 scroll-mt-24 p-6" id="remove">
      <h2 class="flex items-center gap-2.5 text-lg font-semibold">
        <span class="h-2.5 w-2.5 rounded-full bg-openai"></span>
        Remove access when you're done
      </h2>
      <ol class="mt-3 list-decimal space-y-2 pl-5 text-sm leading-relaxed text-body">
        <li>
          Open <a class="link" href="https://platform.openai.com/api-keys">platform.openai.com/api-keys</a>,
          find the key you created, and choose <strong>Revoke</strong>. It stops working
          immediately.
        </li>
        <li>
          In the extension, open <strong>Settings → OpenAI</strong> and clear the saved key (or
          turn the provider off).
        </li>
      </ol>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-body">
        OpenAI has no command-line tool for key management; keys are created and revoked only
        on the dashboard.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Troubleshooting -->
    <section class="mt-12 scroll-mt-24" id="troubleshooting">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Troubleshooting</h2>
      <div class="card mt-4 divide-y divide-edge-soft">
        <TroubleshootItem title='"Credentials are missing or invalid"'>
          <p>
            Double-check the key you pasted; a stray space is the most common cause. Check the
            key wasn't revoked and that your account has billing set up or remaining credits.
            Then click <strong>Save &amp; test</strong> again.
          </p>
        </TroubleshootItem>
        <TroubleshootItem title='"Access denied" or rate-limit errors'>
          <p>
            Verify your account is in good standing, has remaining credits, and hasn't exceeded
            its rate limits. Limits rise automatically as your usage grows.
          </p>
        </TroubleshootItem>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-body">
        For no audio, missing voices, or keyboard shortcut problems, see the
        <a class="link" href="../../troubleshooting/">troubleshooting guide</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <p class="mt-10 text-sm leading-relaxed text-body">
      Prefer a different provider? See
      <a class="link" href="../polly/">Amazon Polly</a>,
      <a class="link" href="../azure/">Azure Speech</a>, or
      <a class="link" href="../google/">Google Cloud TTS</a>.
    </p>
  </main>
</Base>
